The paper deals with image style transfer, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The specific focus on comic styles suggests that graphics (cs.GR) may also be relevant. The use of neural networks for style transfer indicates that artificial intelligence (cs.AI) may be another relevant sub-category. The paper also involves quantitative analysis, which suggests multimedia (cs.MM) may be relevant. Finally, the survey conducted in the paper involves human perception, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) may also be relevant.
